<Link id="l00009" /><CodeLine lineNumber="9"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// This file implements the LiveRange and LiveInterval classes.  Given some</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00010" /><CodeLine lineNumber="10"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// numbering of each the machine instructions an interval &#91;i, j) is said to be a</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00011" /><CodeLine lineNumber="11"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// live range for register v if there is no instruction with number j&#39; &gt;= j</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00012" /><CodeLine lineNumber="12"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// such that v is live at j&#39; and there is no instruction with number i&#39; &lt; i such</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00013" /><CodeLine lineNumber="13"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// that v is live at i&#39;. In this implementation ranges can have holes,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00014" /><CodeLine lineNumber="14"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// i.e. a range might look like &#91;1,20), &#91;50,65), &#91;1000,1001).  Each</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00015" /><CodeLine lineNumber="15"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// individual segment is represented as an instance of LiveRange::Segment,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00016" /><CodeLine lineNumber="16"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// and the whole range is represented as an instance of LiveRange.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00017" /><CodeLine lineNumber="17"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00838" /><CodeLine lineNumber="838"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">    /// Refines the subranges to support \\p LaneMask. This may only be called</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00839" /><CodeLine lineNumber="839"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">    /// for LI.hasSubrange()==true. Subregister ranges are split or created</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00840" /><CodeLine lineNumber="840"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">    /// until \\p LaneMask can be matched exactly. \\p Mod is executed on the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00841" /><CodeLine lineNumber="841"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">    /// matching subranges.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00842" /><CodeLine lineNumber="842"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">    ///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00843" /><CodeLine lineNumber="843"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">    /// Example:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00844" /><CodeLine lineNumber="844"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">    ///    Given an interval with subranges with lanemasks L0F00, L00F0 and</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00845" /><CodeLine lineNumber="845"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">    ///    L000F, refining for mask L0018. Will split the L00F0 lane into</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00846" /><CodeLine lineNumber="846"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">    ///    L00E0 and L0010 and the L000F lane into L0007 and L0008. The Mod</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00847" /><CodeLine lineNumber="847"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">    ///    function will be applied to the L0010 and L0008 subranges.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00848" /><CodeLine lineNumber="848"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">    ///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00849" /><CodeLine lineNumber="849"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">    /// \\p Indexes and \\p TRI are required to clean up the VNIs that</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00850" /><CodeLine lineNumber="850"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">    /// don&#39;t define the related lane masks after they get shrunk. E.g.,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00851" /><CodeLine lineNumber="851"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">    /// when L000F gets split into L0007 and L0008 maybe only a subset</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00852" /><CodeLine lineNumber="852"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">    /// of the VNIs that defined L000F defines L0007.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00853" /><CodeLine lineNumber="853"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">    ///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00854" /><CodeLine lineNumber="854"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">    /// The clean up of the VNIs need to look at the actual instructions</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00855" /><CodeLine lineNumber="855"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">    /// to decide what is or is not live at a definition point. If the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00856" /><CodeLine lineNumber="856"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">    /// update of the subranges occurs while the IR does not reflect these</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00857" /><CodeLine lineNumber="857"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">    /// changes, \\p ComposeSubRegIdx can be used to specify how the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00858" /><CodeLine lineNumber="858"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">    /// definition are going to be rewritten.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00859" /><CodeLine lineNumber="859"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">    /// E.g., let say we want to merge:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00860" /><CodeLine lineNumber="860"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">    ///     V1.sub1:&lt;2 x s32&gt; = COPY V2.sub3:&lt;4 x s32&gt;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00861" /><CodeLine lineNumber="861"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">    /// We do that by choosing a class where sub1:&lt;2 x s32&gt; and sub3:&lt;4 x s32&gt;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00862" /><CodeLine lineNumber="862"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">    /// overlap, i.e., by choosing a class where we can find &quot;offset + 1 == 3&quot;.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00863" /><CodeLine lineNumber="863"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">    /// Put differently we align V2&#39;s sub3 with V1&#39;s sub1:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00864" /><CodeLine lineNumber="864"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">    /// V2: sub0 sub1 sub2 sub3</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00865" /><CodeLine lineNumber="865"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">    /// V1: &lt;offset&gt;  sub0 sub1</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00866" /><CodeLine lineNumber="866"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">    ///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00867" /><CodeLine lineNumber="867"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">    /// This offset will look like a composed subregidx in the class:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00868" /><CodeLine lineNumber="868"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">    ///     V1.(composed sub2 with sub1):&lt;4 x s32&gt; = COPY V2.sub3:&lt;4 x s32&gt;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00869" /><CodeLine lineNumber="869"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">    /// =&gt;  V1.(composed sub2 with sub1):&lt;4 x s32&gt; = COPY V2.sub3:&lt;4 x s32&gt;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00870" /><CodeLine lineNumber="870"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">    ///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00871" /><CodeLine lineNumber="871"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">    /// Now if we didn&#39;t rewrite the uses and def of V1, all the checks for V1</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00872" /><CodeLine lineNumber="872"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">    /// need to account for this offset.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00873" /><CodeLine lineNumber="873"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">    /// This happens during coalescing where we update the live-ranges while</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00874" /><CodeLine lineNumber="874"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">    /// still having the old IR around because updating the IR on-the-fly</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00875" /><CodeLine lineNumber="875"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">    /// would actually clobber some information on how the live-ranges that</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00876" /><CodeLine lineNumber="876"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">    /// are being updated look like.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00877" /><CodeLine lineNumber="877"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">void</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/liveinterval/#a967540f5e5799b56c6fbcee378d110eb">refineSubRanges</a>(<a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#a8e612822d4ba7bb36c9c79582a567108">BumpPtrAllocator</a> &amp;<a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/codegen/regallocbasic-cpp/#ad5d00e1d77644d95847b9bf8da12b759">Allocator</a>, <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/lanebitmask">LaneBitmask</a> LaneMask,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00878" /><CodeLine lineNumber="878"><span class="doxyHighlight">                         std::function&lt;</span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">void</span><span class="doxyHighlight">(<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/liveinterval/subrange">LiveInterval::SubRange</a> &amp;)&gt; Apply,</span></CodeLine>
